{#
  hx-checkbox — Drupal Twig Template
  =====================================

  Server-renders the hx-checkbox custom element with correct attributes.
  Form association is handled automatically via ElementInternals — no Drupal behavior
  is required for standard form submission patterns.

  Note on hx-size: The size attribute is prefixed as `hx-size` to avoid conflicts with the
  native HTML `size` attribute on form elements. If your project uses htmx, note that htmx
  reserves `hx-*` attribute names for its own directives. The `hx-size` attribute on this
  component does not conflict with any current htmx directive, but be aware of this
  namespace overlap when combining HELiX components with htmx on the same page. This
  naming will be normalized in a future major version.

  Parameters:
    label      (string)  Required. Visible label text for the checkbox.
    name       (string)  Required for form submission. The form field name.
    value      (string)  Optional. Value submitted when checked. Defaults to 'on'.
    checked    (bool)    Optional. Pre-renders the checkbox in the checked state.
                         Use for server-side persistence of checkbox state.
    disabled   (bool)    Optional. Renders the checkbox in a disabled state.
    required   (bool)    Optional. Marks the checkbox as required for form submission.
    error      (string)  Optional. Error message displayed below the checkbox.
    help_text  (string)  Optional. Help text displayed below the checkbox.
    size       (string)  Optional. One of: sm | md | lg. Defaults to 'md'.
                         Rendered as the `hx-size` attribute on the element.
    aria_label (string)  Optional. Accessible name when no visible label is provided
                         (e.g., in a custom label slot pattern). Forwarded to the inner input.
    attributes (object)  Optional. Additional HTML attributes spread onto the element.

  Slots (Twig blocks):
    default   — Custom label content. Overrides the `label` parameter. Rich HTML is
                allowed — Drupal can include links or formatted text in consent labels.
    help_text — Custom help text content. Overrides the `help_text` parameter.
    error     — Custom error content. Overrides the `error` parameter.

  Usage examples:

    Simple checkbox:
      {% include 'hx-checkbox.twig' with {
        label: 'Send appointment reminders',
        name: 'reminders',
        value: '1',
      } %}

    Pre-checked with server state:
      {% include 'hx-checkbox.twig' with {
        label: 'Patient consented to treatment',
        name: 'consent',
        value: 'yes',
        checked: node.field_consent.value,
        required: true,
      } %}

    With error state (form validation failure):
      {% include 'hx-checkbox.twig' with {
        label: 'I agree to the terms and conditions',
        name: 'terms',
        required: true,
        error: 'You must accept the terms to continue.',
      } %}

    With help text:
      {% include 'hx-checkbox.twig' with {
        label: 'Enable two-factor authentication',
        name: 'two_factor',
        help_text: 'Adds an extra layer of security to your account.',
      } %}

    Small size (compact lists):
      {% include 'hx-checkbox.twig' with {
        label: 'Hypertension',
        name: 'conditions[]',
        value: 'hypertension',
        size: 'sm',
      } %}

  Drupal behavior for change events:
    The component dispatches an `hx-change` CustomEvent (bubbles, composed) with
    detail `{ checked: boolean, value: string }` when the checkbox state changes.
    For standard form submission, no behavior is needed.
    For AJAX-driven patterns:

      (function (Drupal, once) {
        Drupal.behaviors.helixCheckbox = {
          attach: function (context) {
            once('hx-checkbox-change', 'hx-checkbox[data-ajax]', context).forEach((cb) => {
              cb.addEventListener('hx-change', (e) => {
                // e.detail.checked — new checked state
                // e.detail.value — configured value
                Drupal.ajax({ url: cb.dataset.ajax }).execute();
              });
            });
          },
        };
      })(Drupal, once);
#}

<hx-checkbox
  label="{{ label }}"
  {% if name %}name="{{ name }}"{% endif %}
  {% if value is defined and value != 'on' %}value="{{ value }}"{% endif %}
  {% if checked %}checked{% endif %}
  {% if disabled %}disabled{% endif %}
  {% if required %}required{% endif %}
  {% if error %}error="{{ error }}"{% endif %}
  {% if help_text %}help-text="{{ help_text }}"{% endif %}
  hx-size="{{ size|default('md') }}"
  {% if aria_label %}aria-label="{{ aria_label }}"{% endif %}
  {% for key, val in attributes|default({}) %}{{ key }}="{{ val }}" {% endfor %}
>
  {% block default %}{% endblock %}
  {% if help_text_slot is defined %}
    <span slot="help-text">{{ help_text_slot }}</span>
  {% endif %}
  {% if error_slot is defined %}
    <span slot="error">{{ error_slot }}</span>
  {% endif %}
</hx-checkbox>
